Create a premium mobile app UI concept for a construction-material ordering app called StoneRate. The screen should be the “Place New Order” page for a buyer ordering crushed stone.

Design style:
- Dark amber/orange theme inspired by stone mines, quarry lighting, and premium 3D glass UI.
- Background should feel like a modern mining/construction marketplace: dark brown/black gradient, subtle stone texture, warm orange glow, soft depth, no real photos unless stylized.
- Use glassmorphism cards, 3D-style panels, glowing orange highlights, soft shadows, rounded corners.
- The tone should match a premium mobile app, not a basic form.
- Portrait mobile screen, realistic app layout, full-screen smartphone UI.
- No real brand logos, no copied screenshot elements, no watermark.

Main screen content:
1. Top header:
   - Left side: menu hamburger icon.
   - Center/left text: “Place New Order”.
   - Small subtitle: “Choose material and quantity”.
   - Right side: small notification/profile circular icon.
   - Header should feel clean and premium.

2. Buyer greeting/status area:
   - Small badge: “NEW REQUEST”.
   - Main heading: “What stone do you need today?”
   - Subtext: “Select material, quantity, trucks and delivery site.”

3. Material selection section:
   - A large glass card titled “Select Material”.
   - Show selectable material chips/cards:
     - 20mm Stone
     - 40mm Stone
     - Dust
     - M-Sand
   - One material should be highlighted with orange glow.
   - Use small stone/rock icons or abstract material icons.

4. Quantity section:
   - Glass panel/card titled “Quantity”.
   - Show tons input visually:
     - “40 tons”
     - plus and minus circular buttons.
   - Include a small helper text: “Approx. quantity required”.
   - Make this area look interactive and premium.

5. Truck section:
   - Glass card titled “Truck Requirement”.
   - Show:
     - “2 Trucks”
     - “20 tons each”
   - Include plus/minus controls or stepper style.
   - Add a small 3D truck icon or minimal truck glyph.

6. Delivery location section:
   - Glass card titled “Delivery Site”.
   - Show example location:
     - “Site Location”
     - “Bengaluru East”
   - Include map pin icon and “Change” button.
   - Should feel like the buyer can select saved address.

7. Date/time section:
   - Small glass pill or card:
     - “Required by”
     - “Tomorrow, 10 AM”
   - Calendar/time icon.

8. Notes section:
   - Compact field:
     - “Add note for supplier”
   - Keep it minimal; should not dominate the page.

9. Bottom action area:
   - Large orange primary button:
     - “Submit Rate Request”
   - Secondary small text below:
     - “We’ll check the best available rate and notify you.”
   - Button should have strong orange glow and premium rounded style.

Visual hierarchy:
- Form should not look boring; it should look like a 3D guided ordering flow.
- Use layered glass cards with subtle depth.
- Use orange accent consistently.
- Keep readability high.
- Make the page feel like a real mobile app screen, not a website.
- No excessive text.
- Avoid clutter; use clean spacing.

Composition:
- Portrait phone screen.
- Top header, main content scrollable feel, fixed bottom CTA area.
- Use modern fintech/marketplace app visual quality.
- Dark background with warm orange glow.
- White text, amber highlights, grey secondary text.
- All cards should have rounded corners, soft blur, and depth.
- The final image should show only this one page: “Place New Order”.
